Global Low-speed Automotive Autonomous Emergency Braking System (AEBS) Market Insights
Low-speed Automotive Autonomous Emergency Braking System (AEBS) Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 17.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Low-speed Automotive Autonomous Emergency Braking System (AEBS) Market Overview
The global low-speed automotive Autonomous Emergency Braking System (AEBS) market is valued at USD 1.5 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 3.5 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 18% from 2025 to 2030. The increasing adoption of safety technologies in passenger vehicles, along with advancements in sensor technologies, are driving market growth. OEMs (Original Equipment Manufacturers) are increasingly integrating AEBS as standard features in vehicles, aiming to enhance safety standards and comply with regulatory mandates. The rising awareness among consumers regarding road safety, coupled with government regulations supporting automotive safety innovations, is also fostering market growth. The market is witnessing a shift toward the incorporation of more advanced sensors and AI-powered technologies to improve the performance and efficiency of AEBS systems in low-speed scenarios.

